name: Catan
details: Catan is a multiplayer board game where players attempt to build and develop holdings while trading and acquiring resources. Players gain points as their settlements grow; the first to reach a set number of points wins.

name: Monopoly
details: Monopoly is a board game in which players roll two six-sided dice to move around the game board, buying and trading properties, and developing them with houses and hotels. Players collect rent from their opponents, with the goal being to drive them into bankruptcy.

name: Risk
details: Risk is a strategy board game of diplomacy, conflict, and conquest for two to six players. The standard version is played on a board depicting a political map of the Earth, divided into forty-two territories, which are grouped into six continents.

name: Chess
details: Chess is a two-player strategy board game played on a checkered board with 64 squares arranged in an 8×8 grid. The game is played by millions of people worldwide.

name: Pandemic
details: Pandemic is a cooperative board game in which players work as a team to treat infections around the world while gathering resources for cures.

name: Ticket to Ride
details: Ticket to Ride is a cross-country train adventure game in which players collect train cards to claim railway routes connecting cities throughout North America.

name: Carcassonne
details: Carcassonne is a tile-placement game in which players draw and place a tile with a piece of southern French landscape on it. The tile might feature a city, a road, a cloister, grassland or some combination thereof, and it must be placed adjacent to tiles that have already been played.

name: 7 Wonders
details: 7 Wonders is a civilization-building card game that is played using three decks of cards featuring depictions of ancient civilizations, military conflicts, and commercial activity. The game is divided into three ages, and players draft cards to build their civilization.

name: Splendor
description: A game of gem collection and trading.
details: Splendor is a game of chip-collecting and card development. Players are merchants of the Renaissance trying to buy gem mines, means of transportation, shops—all in order to acquire the most prestige points.

name: Dominion
details: Dominion is a deck-building card game where players use a random set of cards to build a deck with which to buy provinces, duchies, and estates. The player with the most victory points wins.

name: Codenames
details: Codenames is a word-based party game where players split into two teams, each with a spymaster who gives one-word clues to their teammates to guess the words correctly.

name: Terraforming Mars
description: A strategy game set on Mars.
details: In Terraforming Mars, players take the role of corporations working together to terraform the planet Mars by raising the temperature, creating oceans, and forming forests.

name: Gloomhaven
details: Gloomhaven is a cooperative game of tactical combat in a unique, evolving world. Players take on the role of wandering adventurers with special skills and reasons for traveling to this dark corner of the world.

name: Wingspan
details: Wingspan is a competitive, medium-weight, card-driven, engine-building board game in which players work to attract birds to their wildlife reserves.

name: Azul
description: A tile-laying game inspired by Portuguese tiles.
details: Azul is a tile-laying game where players collect tiles to complete a pattern on their player board while scoring points based on the patterns and sets they create.

name: Scythe
description: An engine-building game set in an alternate-history 1920s.
details: Scythe is an engine-building game set in an alternate-history 1920s period. It is a time of farming and war, broken hearts and rusted gears, innovation and valor.

name: Agricola
details: Agricola is a game of farming and resource management. Players start with a small farm and gradually expand it by planting crops, raising animals, and upgrading their home.

name: Betrayal at House on the Hill
description: A cooperative game with a traitor element.
details: Betrayal at House on the Hill is a cooperative game where players explore a haunted house until one of them turns traitor and the rest must work together to defeat the traitor's evil plot.

name: Twilight Struggle
description: A two-player strategy game set during the Cold War.
details: Twilight Struggle is a two-player game where one player takes the role of the United States and the other takes the role of the Soviet Union in a struggle for global dominance during the Cold War.
